label.value: Protein Hormone Receptor

value.value: Typically associated with the cell membrane, Protein Hormone Receptors selectively bind with high affinity to genetically-encoded polymerized amino acids in peptide linkage that have regulatory effects on the activity of specific target cells. A ligand-induced conformational and functional change in the receptor alters its interaction with target molecules, leading to changes in cellular physiology through modification of the activity of signal transduction pathways.

label.value: TRANK1 Gene

value.value: This gene may be involved in immune response-related signal regulation.

label.value: TRANK1 wt Allele

value.value: Human TRANK1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p22.2 and is approximately 119 kb in length. This allele, which encodes TPR and ankyrin repeat-containing protein 1, may play a role in immunity. Genetic variation within the 3' region of this gene locus may be associated with Kleine-Levin syndrome (KLS) and susceptibility for bipolar depressive disorder.

label.value: TPR and Ankyrin Repeat-Containing Protein 1

value.value: TPR and ankyrin repeat-containing protein 1 (2925 aa, ~336 kDa) is encoded by the human TRANK1 gene. This protein may be involved in immune response-mediated signaling.

label.value: Tetratricopeptide Repeat

value.value: A protein binding motif consisting of repeats of a degenerate 34 amino acid sequence. These sequences can be found individually and dispersed in the protein sequence or as arrays of 3-16 tandem repeats. Tetratricopeptide (TPR) repeats have a paired alpha helical structure and the pairs can form higher order structural domains that are involved in protein-protein interactions.

label.value: Circulating Deoxyribonucleotide

value.value: Deoxyribonucleotides (comprised of a deoxyribose sugar, a nitrogenous base, and one, two or three phosphoryl groups) found in the circulation.

label.value: Circulating Cell-Free Human Papillomavirus DNA

label.value: Cumulative Illness Rating Scale for Geriatrics Clinical Classification

value.value: A clinical assessment tool designed to measure comorbidity in geriatric cancer patients. The tool grades comorbidity severity from 0-4 in 14 organ systems: Heart; Vascular; Hematopoietic; Respiratory; Eyes, ears, nose, throat, and larynx; Upper GI; Lower GI; Liver, pancreas, and biliary; Renal; Genitourinary; Musculoskeletal and skin; Neurologic; Endocrine and breast; Psychiatric illness.

label.value: Allogeneic Anti-CD19/CD22 CAR-BBz T-cells

value.value: A preparation of allogeneic T-lymphocytes that have been transduced with a bivalent lentiviral vector encoding a chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) targeting the two tumor-associated antigens (TAAs) CD19 and CD22, linked to the co-stimulatory domain 4-1BB (CD137) coupled to the zeta chain of the TCR/CD3 complex (TCRzeta; CD247; CD3zeta), with potential immunostimulating and antineoplastic activities. Upon administration, the allogeneic anti-CD19/CD22 CAR-BBz T-cells bind to and induce selective toxicity in tumor cells expressing CD19 and CD22. CD19 and CD22, both transmembrane phosphoglycoproteins expressed on the surface of cells in the B lineage, are often overexpressed on malignant B-cells. By simultaneously targeting two B-cell antigens, this preparation may minimize relapse due to single antigen loss in patients with B-cell malignancies.
